description: Featuring five all-new, all-original comic book stories, plus DVD-style commentary and sketches from five of the industry's top talents! This new sketchbook, from the medium's best, features each artist creating their own new, original story! A must for comic art fans!

description:
A New 52 title starring a new version of the Justice League of America recruited by director of A.R.G.U.S. Amanda Waller and led by A.R.G.U.S. member Steve Trevor, consisting of Green Lantern (Simon Baz), Martian Manhunter, Green Arrow, Stargirl, Catwoman, Hawkman, Katana and Vibe. It was later revealed that the League was assembled to combat the original Justice League, if it is ever required.

The first issue launched with a total of 54 total different covers, the United States flag cover, covers for each 50 states, as well as Washington DC and Puerto Rico.

The title also contains a Martian Manhunter back up starting within the second issue.

The series was concluded following the Forever Evil story arc.

Main Feature:

  • Written by: Geoff Johns (#1 - Present); Jeff Lemire (#6 - 7); Matt Kindt (#8 - 14)
  • Illustrated by: David Finch (#1 - 3); Brett Booth (#4 - 5); Doug Mahnke (#6 - 7, 8); Tom Derenick (#9 - 10); Eddy Barrows (#10 - 13)

Back-up feature:

  • Written by: Matt Kindt (#2 - 5)
  • Illustrated by: Scott Clark (#2); Manuel Garcia (#3 - 5)

Villain Month

  1. Justice League of America #7.1 - Deadshot #1
  2. Justice League of America #7.2 - Killer Frost #1
  3. Justice League of America #7.3 - Shadow Thief #1
  4. Justice League of America #7.4 - Black Adam #1

Collected Editions

  • Justice League of America: World's Most Dangerous (#1-5)
  • Justice League: Trinity War (#6-7)
  • DC Comics The New 52 Villains Omnibus (#7.1-7.4)
  • Suicide Squad: Discipline and Punish (#7.1)
  • Justice League of America: Survivors of Evil (#8-14)
name: Justice League of America

description:
Nova Volume 5

A Marvel NOW! title starring a new Nova, the young boy named Sam Alexander. The first Nova series starring a different person than Richard Rider. The series lasted for a total of issue 31 after which the series ended due to the events of Secret Wars. After Secret Wars, the series was resumed with a new number 1 in Nova Volume 6. The series also had a special Nova Annual issue.

Written by Jeph Loeb (#1-5), Zeb Wells (#6-10), Gerry Duggan (#10-)

Illustrated by Ed McGuinness (#1-5), Paco Medina (#6-), Carlo Barberi (#10).

Collected Editions

  • Nova: Origin (#1-5)
  • Nova: Rookie Season (#6-9 and material from #10)
  • Infinity Companion (#8-9)
  • Nova: Nova Corpse (#11-15 and material from #10)
  • Original Sin Companion (#18-20)
  • Nova: AXIS (#23-27)
  • Guardians of the Galaxy & X-Men: The Black Vortex (#28)
  • Nova: Homecoming (#28-31)

Translated into Spanish.
